  "text": "1. Alcohol Use Disorders Identification Test (AUDIT) The AUDIT [CITATION_1] is a 10-item self-assessment questionnaire that presents good sensitivity and specificity for the screening of excessive alcohol use and dependence [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The first three questions of the AUDIT assess frequency and quantity of alcohol use. AUDIT has been translated and validated in the French language [CITATION_5] . According to the cutoff values in the French validation, three groups can be identified:",
